title: 820-3115-B green light, no boot
message:
Hi, got an 820-3115-B with green light, no boot

PPBUS_G3H: 12.53 v

PP3V42_G3H: 3.47v

PP5V_S5: 0v

PP3V3_S5: 0v

Diode mode to ground PP5V_S5: 0

U7200 is getting hot, but removing it does not take the short away. Near caps arent getting hot.

title: 820-3115-B green light, no boot
message:
Remove L5800, R5805 and check again.
Also check C7273 and C5800.

Don't forget U/C7801.

title: 820-3115-B green light, no boot
message:
U5805 was shorted.

Now i have fan spin, HDD light but no image and no chime.

Now i have every rail but PPVCORE_S0_CPU (0v)

title: 820-3115-B green light, no boot

Just in case, change U7400.
What is the resistance to ground (ohm scale) at L7510/50?

title: 820-3115-B green light, no boot
message:
Be sure all surrounding resistors and traces are good.
Try known good BIOS.

title: 820-3115-B green light, no boot
